column24: Repairing the infrastructure to resist earthquakes and natural disasters and providing decent housing for villages and mountainous areas that live in mud houses, as information has been found about the areas that build their houses from mud. This is due to the fact that the authorities prevent them from urban construction and building with stone, but are forced to build them with mud. To attract tourists, since the purpose of tourists to visit these areas is to see the residents who live in houses made of mud and dirt, so the residents are prevented from urban construction (Al-Sass and Lebrik) in order to attract foreign tourism. This is what we need in Morocco, as well as providing decent education and hospitals capable of accommodating victims. Natural disasters and so on make it difficult to treat patients with high technologies, as in public hospitals you find that even a scanner or radio is not available.

column4: منطقة قشيش - جماعة المدينة - عمالة مراكش
column10:
السلام عليكم ورحمة الله. 
اشكركم على هذه المبادرة الإنسانية النبيلة، أنا أعمل بثانوية الموحدين التأهيلية التي تقع في منطقة قشيش جماعة المدينة بمراكش و التي تعاني من هشاشة اجتماعية، و إثر هذه الهزة الزلزالية تضررت العديد من الأسر بعد انهيار منازلهم او بعدما اصبحت منازلهم آيلة للسقوط، حيث حاليا منهم من يبيت في المأوى الذي أنشأه المجلس الجماعي لمدينة مراكش بملعب 20 غشت بمنطقة قشيش و منهم من يبيت في خيام على الرصيف المحادي لسور المدينة العتيقة و منهم من لجأ إلى أقاربه, و في ثانويتنا أطلقنا مبادرة تبرع لمد يد المساعدة لهم و انا اقترحت على زملائي بالثانوية البحث عن وسيلة لاقتناء اللوازم المدرسية بما أننا لازلنا في فترة الدخول المدرسي و قد تم استئناف  الدراسة. طرقت باب بعض الجمعيات لهذا الغرض لكن لم أتلق بعد اي رد لحد الساعة. و اتمنى ان تستجيبوا انتم لطلبي و لكم جزيل الشكر.
column26: Qashish area - Medina Community - Marrakesh Prefecture
column31:
Peace and mercy of God.
Thank you for this noble humanitarian initiative. I work at Almohad Rehabilitation Secondary School, which is located in the Qashish area of ​​the Medina community in Marrakesh, which suffers from social fragility. As a result of this earthquake, many families were affected after their homes collapsed or after their homes became destined to collapse, as some of them are currently living in poverty. He sleeps in the shelter established by the Collective Council of the City of Marrakesh in the August 20 stadium in the Qashish area. Some of them sleep in tents on the sidewalk adjacent to the wall of the ancient city, and some of them take refuge with their relatives. In our high school, we launched a donation initiative to extend a helping hand to them, and I suggested to my high school classmates to research About a way to purchase school supplies since we are still in the school entry period and studies have resumed. I knocked on the doors of some associations for this purpose, but I have not received any response yet. I hope that you will respond to my request, and I thank you very much.

الوضع مزري هناك 3 دواوير بجماعة سكورة اقليم ورزازات متضررة بشدة أزيد من نصف ساكة هذة الدواوير تعيش خارح منازلها سواء في خيام او في العراء نظرا لان النازل سقطت جزئيا أو تعرضت لاضرار خطيرة واصبحت معرضة للسقوط في أي لحضة مما يشكل خكرا على الساكنة رغم الجعود التي قامت بها الجمعيات المحلية في توفير خيام جماعية لكن تبقى غير كافية وللاسف لخد الان لم تصل اي مساعدات لهذه الدواوير عدا هذا الصباح وصلت بعض المساعدات من السلطة المخلية لكنها قليلة جدا .
ابمشكل الرئيسي الذي يقلق الساكنة هو مشكل الايواء بالدرجة الأولى
column31:
The situation is dire. There are 3 villages in the Skoura community, Ouarzazate province, that are severely damaged. More than half of the residents of these villages live outside their homes, whether in tents or in the open, because the houses have partially fallen or been exposed to serious damage and are at risk of collapsing at any moment, which constitutes a hideout for the residents despite the hunger that has arisen. Local associations are able to provide collective tents, but they remain insufficient. Unfortunately, until now, no aid has arrived to these circles. Except this morning, some aid arrived from the internal authority, but it is very little.
The main problem that worries the residents is primarily the problem of shelter

column31:
What can I say? There is no power nor strength except with God, the Most High, the Great. Elderly men, women and children living with weak capabilities. Mothers crying with tears of heartbreak. Blood at the loss of loved ones. Entire families have passed away. We belong to God and to Him we shall return.
 Material and human losses due to the earthquake. Most of the houses are demolished and others are subject to demolition. We ask philanthropists and people of good conscience to provide a helping hand to those in need, because the officials in this department are in a deep slumber.
 I have never seen such a scene in my life that breaks the heart. Praise be to Him who pardoned us from what He afflicted them with and favored us over many of those He created.

column10:
الناس يحتاجون الملابس والخيم (مأوى) خصوصا للنساء والأطفال لأن المنازل انهارت وفقد الناس كل شيء خصوصا في هذه الدواوير: (دوار تابيا، داور بوخالف، دوار تارغونت، دوار كاطوس، دوار تالوين، دوار أگني، دوار امي ودرك، دوار اركراكن، دوار وجدان، دوار اعوفين، دوار اماسين، دوار بوخالف) أغلبية هذه الدواوير انهدمت منازلها والناس يعيشون في عراء دون مأوى.
المرجو إرسال المساعدات والتأكد أنها وصلت إلى عين المكان، توجد طريق يوصل إلى هذه الدواوير قرب مقر جماعة الزاوية النحلية على اليسار عند الإقبال من مراكش على الطريق 212 وعلى اليمين عند الإقبال من إمنتانوت.
column27: Al-Zawiyat al-Nahli community center is on Route 212 leading to Amantanot. You ask via Ehsayniten Road, which leads to the left, which leads to Targunt, Tebia, etc.
column31:
People need clothes and tents (shelter), especially for women and children, because houses collapsed and people lost everything, especially in these roundabouts: (Tabia roundabout, Boukhalef roundabout, Targount roundabout, Katous roundabout, Talouine roundabout, Agne roundabout, Emi and Gendarmerie roundabout, Arkrakne roundabout, Wejdan roundabout. (Aufin roundabout, Amasin roundabout, Boukhalef roundabout). The majority of these roundabouts have had their homes destroyed and people are living in the open without shelter.
Please send aid and make sure that it reaches the place. There is a road that leads to these circles near the headquarters of the Zawiya al-Nahli community, on the left at the entrance from Marrakesh on Route 212, and on the right at the entrance from Imnanot.
